cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.DS

The paper discusses a new adversary model for Location Based Services (LBSs) and proposes a method for tracking a user's position by analyzing encrypted traffic exchanged between the user and the LBS provider. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves data analysis (cs.SI) and cryptography (cs.CY) to some extent. Additionally, the paper uses statistical analysis and machine learning techniques (cs.DS) to analyze the data collected from the location-based app.
